#. <section class="sutta" id="sn6.11"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn6.11:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 6"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 6"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn6.11:0.2"
msgid "2. Dutiyavagga"
msgstr "2. The Second Chapter"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn6.11:0.3"
msgid "11. Sanaṅkumārasutta"
msgstr "11. With Sanaṅkumāra"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn6.11:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

msgctxt "sn6.11:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā rājagahe viharati sappinītīre."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Rājagaha, on the bank of the Sappinī "
"river."

msgctxt "sn6.11:1.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho brahmā sanaṅkumāro abhikkantāya rattiyā abhikkantavaṇṇo "
"kevalakappaṃ sappinītīraṃ obhāsetvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; "
"upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi."
msgstr ""
"Then, late at night, the beautiful Brahmā Sanaṅkumāra, lighting up the "
"entire Sappinī riverbank, went up to the Buddha, bowed, stood to one side,"

msgctxt "sn6.11:1.4"
msgid ""
"Ekamantaṃ ṭhito kho brahmā sanaṅkumāro bhagavato santike imaṃ gāthaṃ abhāsi:"
msgstr "and recited this verse in the Buddha’s presence:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.332"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn6.11:2.1"
msgid "“Khattiyo seṭṭho janetasmiṃ,"
msgstr "“The aristocrat is best of those people"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn6.11:2.2"
msgid "ye gottapaṭisārino;"
msgstr "who take clan as the standard."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn6.11:2.3"
msgid "Vijjācaraṇasampanno,"
msgstr "But one accomplished in knowledge and conduct"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn6.11:2.4"
msgid "so seṭṭho devamānuse”ti."
msgstr "is best of gods and humans.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn6.11:3.1"
msgid "Idamavoca brahmā sanaṅkumāro."
msgstr "That’s what Brahmā Sanaṅkumāra said,"

msgctxt "sn6.11:3.2"
msgid "Samanuñño satthā ahosi."
msgstr "and the teacher approved."

msgctxt "sn6.11:3.3"
msgid ""
"Atha kho brahmā sanaṅkumāro “samanuñño me satthā”ti bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā "
"padakkhiṇaṃ katvā tatthevantaradhāyīti."
msgstr ""
"Then Brahmā Sanaṅkumāra, knowing that the teacher approved, bowed and "
"respectfully circled the Buddha, keeping him on his right, before vanishing "
"right there."
